title.narrative: Revenue Administration and Revenue Policy - Gambia. Revenue Policy and Administration - The Gambia. Revenue Administration and Revenue Policy - The Gambia

description.narrative: Support the establishment of a sound private, well-functioning, equitable financial sector that fulfills critical roles in a market economy, most importantly financial intermediation – the efficient generation and allocation of savings to their most productive use.

This award strives to support the establishment of a sound private, well-functioning, equitable financial sector that fulfills critical roles in a market economy. More specifically, this includes OTA will assist the Gambia Revenue Authority on improving taxpayer registration, internal audit, investigations, and risk management.. Project was canceled.. OTA provided initial TA to the Gambia Revenue Authority on taxpayer registration, cleaning up the registration database, assigning business codes, and reviewing procedures for processing taxpayer ID registrations. Additional assistance is on hold pending further coordination with the GRA and IMF.. OTA is providing initial TA to the Gambia Revenue Authority on taxpayer registration, cleaning up the registration database, assigning business codes, and reviewing procedures for processing taxpayer ID registrations. Assistance in internal affairs, internal audit, risk management, and operational management, and strategic planning is slated to begin in 2019.. Project definition awaits TADAT assessment Q1 2018. Likely to target audit and debt management..
